Validators run on 10gbps link
Ahh OK

Does latency matter?  @chaindude For example two identical servers located on two different continents. Obviously they will have a significant difference in terms of latency, depending on where they connect to

For example latency between North America and Europe is usually in the triple digit milliseconds. If that matters and if most validators are located in North America, people in Europe and elsewhere will stand no chance
Let's consider latency. Benchmarks are affected by latency now.

Yeah I’m looking at the source code. We can fix the problem by first sending miners a small payload. Do it a few times to establish the average baseline latency. Then it’s just a matter of substracting the latency time from the benchmark response time
